<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Infectious" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Infectious,</orth> 1) having the plague: <cit><quote>like one i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.99" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 99</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the i. house,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 21</bibl></cit> (Qq <emph>infected</emph>).<lb />2) communicating a disease, contagious: <cit><quote>a huge i. troop of pale distemperatures,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 81</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the i. pestilence,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 2, 10</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 1, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.5.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 5, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 5, 26</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>